column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/a5e685bcf8eea088ba2eea544dcf2b0ac29ff6cc for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/cu

Here's the address assignments page from IANA: https://www.iana.org/assignments/ipv6-unicast-address-assignments/ipv6-unicast-address-assignments.xhtml As you can see 2011: isn't a valid prefix. whois says hurricane electric has 2001:470::, and my IPv6 tunnels I have with them are all in 2001:470::

ACK
2 dev ACKs with valid sources should lead to immediate merge for such small pulls IMHO :).\n
@Diapolo it would have been even better if the submitter of the pull request cites sources\n
@laanwj You are right, perhaps the sources should have been mentioned in the commit-msg also.\n
